NAME
  vserver - manage virtual private servers
SYNOPSIS
  vserver enter [vname]
  vserver exec [vname] [command]
  vserver info [vname]
  vserver procfs [func] [conf]
  vserver start [vname]
  vserver status [vname]
  vserver stop [vname]
DESCRIPTION
  The vserver command is used to manage virtual private servers.

  The script calls the function in the first argument with all remaining
  options as function parameters. See OPTIONS below.
  
  Most functions expect the option vname; the name of the virtual server you
  want to operate on.

  enter   Enter the environment of a virtual server
  exec    Execute a given command inside a virtual server
  info    Show various information about a virtual server
  procfs  Manage filesystem attributes for /proc entries
  start   Start a currently halted virtual server
  status  Show the status of a runnung virtual server
  stop    Stop a currently running virtual server
OPTIONS
  enter  
    vname    Virtual server name
  exec  
    vname    Virtual server name
    command  Command to execute
  info  
    vname    Virtual server name
  procfs  
    func     Function to use (one of: hide, unhide)
    conf     ProcFS configuration file
  start  
    vname    Virtual server name
  status  
    vname    Virtual server name
  stop  
    vname    Virtual server name
EXAMPLE
  Build a new virtual server 'myvps' using the skeleton method:

      $ vserver build -m skeleton myvps

  Start the virtual server 'myvps':

      $ vserver start myvps
